The first virtual service provider will reach Czech Republic this year .
Maybe
The Czech mobile market is relatively developed and our service providers offer the same services as their Western European partners .
Nevertheless , we lack something here - a virtual service provider that forces classical service providers to reduce prices .
Maybe it wo n't be for long .
On the Mobile.cz website we have often written that Czech service providers are among the most expensive in Europe .
This was confirmed by the ČTÚ , which drew attention to the fact that the price of SMS in the Czech Republic is more expensive than the rest of the EU .
After the recent European Commission ’s entry , the roaming charges may therefore be considered to be a controversial situation – some Czech mobile operators ’ clients will be cheaper than domestic text messages .
How is it possible that prices in Czech Republic are so high compared to Europe ?
The answer is simple , we lack competition to fight .
This may sound controversial , because we have three mobile networks and penetration is above 100 % .
On the contrary , mobile operators are eager to complain that the Czech market is extremely competitive .
He often agrees with Pavel Dvořák , President of the Council of the Czech Telecommunications Office , who has stated a few times that there is no room for another provider in the Czech Republic .
Perhaps it is true that the classical provider with its own network probably does not have much chance ( however , it is likely that it would find it difficult to find a frequency ) .
But there is also another option - a virtual provider .
The mobile market entry of virtual service providers has brought a significant price decrease , which the classic service providers had to respond to .
In the meantime , even before the big fish entered the market , such as Tesco Mobile or Virgin Mobile in Britain , sounds like ours .
However , it has been proven that such service providers have a place and can be successful .
However , for example , we do n’t have to go too far .
This February , we informed you about the launch of the Mobilking virtual service provider in Poland .
In less than half a year , this provider managed to acquire more than 100,000 customers and become the fifth largest provider there .
Meanwhile , the Penta financial group is behind Mobilking , which is the owner of U:fon in the Czech Republic .
The advantage of virtual service providers is the possibility of focusing on a much narrower target group .
For efficient operation , you need much less customers than the traditional provider .
It does not entail relatively high construction , mobile network operation and maintenance costs .
Virtual service providers in the world thus usually appear as low cost - they offer cheap calls and text messages , which are often offset by fewer services .
For example , Tesco Mobile from Great Britain offers at least 50 percent cheaper text messages than its competitors .
But as the example of Mobilking in Poland shows , it is quite a good bet to bet on a target group .
This provider is specifically focused on men .
" Real men choose Mobilking providers - who they like , who they can trust , " says David Seibert , CEO of Mobil Entertainment Company , who operates this virtual provider .
It is hard to say whether the idea like Poland can work with us .
Miroslav Čepický , spokesperson for Vodafone , doubts : " The Czech market is relatively small for segmental approach , based on which most virtual service providers are based .
In addition , it is relatively satisfied with the offer of services . "
In the Czech Republic , there is no chance , they claim mobile operators
However , it seems almost certain that if you become a virtual provider in the Czech Republic , it will not be Mobilking .
" We are talking about the successful expansion of this project , but in the Czech Republic the negotiations do not seem to be very hopeful .
Mobilking is launched in other countries of our region , ” said Jana Studničková , spokesperson for the Penta financial group in his phone interview to Mobil.cz .
This indirectly proved that existing mobile operators in the Czech Republic do not have a very similar interest in this idea .
On the contrary , they try to do everything they can to ensure that no potential competition is possible .
The GTS Novera Group has been keeping its interest in launching a virtual service provider for some time , which is therefore trying to take another step to make Telefonica O2 a real competitor on the field of corporate customers .
" We are very interested in providing our customers with not only fixed - line , but mobile telecommunications services .
And the sooner the better .
We have repeatedly discussed this option with all Czech mobile operators .
Some of them have already been able to progress in negotiations , ” says Pavel Kaidl , spokesperson of the group .
Maybe now 's a good time .
Out of official information , it seems that we can be lucky for the first virtual provider by the end of the year .
His birth is still surrounded by an impenetrable wall of silence .
" At this moment we do not think that a full - fledged virtual service provider should be in the Czech market .
The Czech market is very special , unlike other markets .
We have not yet been addressed by an unequal subject offering complex and serious projects in this area , ” said Vlastimil Sršeň , the Telefónica 02 Press Department .
The Czech market is also referred to by other service providers .
Martina Kemrová , spokesperson for T - Mobile , with O2 exceptionally , adds : " So far , we have not recorded any viable and bilaterally beneficial business projects to which it can be based . "
And he added : " In the T - Mobile network by the end of the year , it is unlikely that any virtual provider will appear .
At this moment , we should have a concrete agreement on our table to think in such a short term . "
Vodafone is more focused on meeting its own 3G licensing requirements .
Miroslav Čepický adds : " We are open to negotiations with potential virtual service providers , especially in the area of cost and infrastructure sharing .
This is what we consider the most rewarding for our customers .
The main strategy of Vodafone is to find a partner in this area to build networks shared with the fast mobile internet . "
Responsible agencies - in a string with service providers
The process of mobile operators is easy to understand , the entry of another provider would mean the increase in competition , and thus lead to a decrease in their profits .
So why make it easy to enter such a competition ?
When providers have something important , they can cooperate , testify to the draft of the birth of U:fon .
The greatest pressure on ČTÚ was likely to be around the birth of the U.M. Phone of T - Mobile .
