Opinion - The speech of Barrick Gold orwelli
In the September 17 issue of Le Devoir , a letter was published from Patrick J. Garver , Deputy President and CEO of the Canadian Barrick Gold mine .
In his presentation in Orwell , Garver declares that the world 's largest gold - producing company has launched a six - million dollar libel lawsuit against three authors and a small - money publishing company in order to initiate a so - called " public debate " .
Although judges are independent and impartial , their decision , especially in slander lawsuits , is not made on the basis of justice , but by law .
It 's no surprise Garver was deeply silent about this fundamental difference .
Would the best way to open a public debate for Barrick Gold is to destroy anyone who has a conflicting opinion with his ?
Regardless of the outcome of the trial , authors and publishers of the book Noir Canada must spend significant amounts on defence and struggle in an uneven battle where the other side is supported by an army of lawyers with almost inexhaustible sources of mining industry .
In such an unequal struggle , however , they often use the tactic to destroy the defendant and conclude a friendly agreement , which not only silences the contrary , but also intimidates those who would try to deal with the issue again .
If Barrick Gold really wanted a public debate , he should have expressed his views in public .
Although in many other countries where Barrick Gold operates , this happens differently , in Canada , the parties who argue do not usually punch each other with a stick , but they tell their thoughts .
The mine would therefore have been enough to open its books and dossiers and prepare for a real debate in a press , media , publications , paying for independent research groups that could have shed light on the issue .
But it seems Barrick Gold does n't trust the public , and it 's gon na take a step to mislead the requests and letters written to protect the authors of Noir Canada .
Mr. Garver might explain how to initiate a " public " debate if he does not take the public 's view ?
In the head of the Deputy President , this word probably means only lawyers paid for in a way , not Canada ’s total population : the meaning of the concept is thus narrowed .
In a democratic state , even the other scoundrels are entitled to freedom of speech .
But Barrick Gold does not understand - or does not want to understand that the authors and publishers of Noir Canada are mostly supported by the public because they condemn the rough method of the mine .
The public is prepared to listen to Barrick and make a judgment , but it would be done on the basis of civilized arguments , not by a lawsuit for a lot of people to be silenced . ( In the case of the term " public debate " , Barrick Gold recently called on the authors of Noir Canada to refrain from using this term . )
In addition to Garver 's surreal expositions , Barrick Gold 's process is an open attack on the freedom of university research and the search for truth , which are the building blocks of all democratic societies .
In the whole procedure , it denies the right to quote authentic sources , something about the dispute on facts and their interpretation , which forms the basis of intellectual activities .
If in a country like Canada you can study and discuss topics that are not pleasing to the rich companies of today ’s world , who will take the liberty of doing so ?
If Barrick Gold really wants an open and transparent debate , it could do so by the scientific standards that Noir Canada authors use .
You have the right to answer .
In our university circle we have been able to deal with disputes , differences of views and conflicts for a long time .
The reckless procedure of Barrick Gold shows that , unlike his claim , he does not want to engage in an open debate .
This is a loss for both the world of universities and the institution of public debate in Canada . It is time for governments to implement measures that limit legal proceedings for such abuse .
Wall Street Rescue Mission - The Democrats and Republicans agreed
The Republican and Democratic leaders of the Bush government and Congress finally reached an agreement yesterday on the economic rescue operation , which has been the biggest tailor - made plan since the Great Depression of the 1930s .
The $ 700 billion plan , which aims to stop the financial crisis that has been raging on Wall Street for months , must still be approved by the two houses of Congress .
The main points of the plan : more effective control of implementation by representatives ; new mechanisms to repay the state funds ; new provisions to keep the number of houses booked due to the lack of payments ; access to the payment of the leaders of the companies received from the aid .
Henry Paulson , US Secretary of Finance , Nancy Pelosi , President of the US House of Representatives and Judd Gregg , the Republican representative in the trial , announced the good news a few minutes before midnight after the two - day marathon hearing ended .
“ We have made a great step towards a solution that will work effectively in the markets , ” said Henry Paulson , Bush Government representative .
" We did everything to save the real economy and the American citizens from the current crisis that hit Wall Street , " the Democratic representative explained .
" The most important aspect is that if we do n't do this , then the shock , chaos and confusion in the everyday lives of Americans will be huge , " said Republican representative Judd Gregg .
The trial was accelerated within the last few hours , fearing that another failure would have a detrimental effect on the mood of investors .
They gave themselves a deadline for the settlement until the opening of the stock market this morning .
Two presidential candidates who joined the negotiations were willing to agree , but they expressed themselves , and they were not happy that the situation had increased to the end .
Democratic Senator Barack Obama himself attributed to the extension of the agreement with elements such as the preservation of home property or the payment of the leaders of the companies helped by the state .
" When we ask taxpayers to take certain extraordinary steps due to the irresponsibility of other people , it is not very welcome .
These steps are necessary , " he noted on an American television show .
And when his opponent , John McCain , another channel , asked if he would vote for the proposed plan , he said , " I 'd like to know the details , but I hope so . "
" What I have read in large lines , it is already visible that it is a matter that we all need to digest , and by which we can move forward .
The possibility of doing nothing is simply unacceptable , ” he said .
According to the 700 billionaire plan , taxpayers would buy dubious demands from American financial institutions , some unsustainable assets at risk .
The plan was preceded by a crisis of 14 months , which was triggered by the release of the real estatelufi . This first led to the collapse of risky real estate loans ( secondary mortgages ) , and then spread to other debt securities , and ultimately caused the freezing of liquid resources and the stirring up of banks and financial institutions .
The first draft agreement was failed by a group of Republican representatives last week .
It seems that we 've managed to get out of this dead end since the Democrats agreed to provide some " poisonous " tools for companies in difficult situations rather than the government .
In order to ensure that all members of Congress are satisfied , a provision has been included in the plan , which requires that if the government has to bear losses within the framework of the programme for five years , it may issue new taxes to recover its resources .
As part of the new plan , a $ 250 billion payment would be made ; this could be followed by another $ 100 billion if the president considered it necessary .
The remaining $ 350 billion payout should be approved by Congress by a new vote .
In exchange for the help , Washington will earn a share in the supported companies , which will give him dividends of profits and which he can sell after the crisis is reduced .
The federal government will be able to delay the seizure of properties that cover the mortgages covered by the plan .
