Psychology of overbilling : why are we issuing more money ?
In auctions , buyers tend to spend more money , overvalue the goods .
The neuroscientific and ecological foundations of this known and seemingly irrational behavior have been revealed by neurologists and economists at the University of New York .
According to their study published in Science , people do not want to miss a competition of the type , such as eBay auction , so they pay too high a price .
He was trying to map this neural scheme of research using experimental auctions .
One group of volunteers was lottery , the other group participated in a player auction , while the functional magnetic resonance ( fMRI ) method was used to study the active brain areas of experimental persons .
In both games , participants could win money , but during the auction game - in which an important element is the overbidation of the other party - the complex under the striatum , which is under the cortex , was intensely activated when the game was lost .
This area of the brain plays a role in the " self - rewarding " mechanism of the nervous system with several other functions .
Therefore , researchers believe that the price is increased by avoiding the intense reaction of striatum .
To support their theory , the members of the research team also conducted a financial follow - up investigation .
In this three groups bid against a partner in various circumstances .
The control group was simply informed of the realistic value of the product concerned and they made their bets .
In addition , another group was promised that if they were won out of the game , they would receive another $ 15 worth of money .
The third group , however , received just 15 dollars before the auction , but the group members lost this money in case of a losing auction .
The difference between the two groups was , therefore , that the win was emphasized for one and for the other , the loss .
However , proving the hypothesis of neurologists , members of the team playing against " loss " were willing to bet higher than the control and the " winning " group .
" These results can not be traced from any earlier economic theory .
They have only explained the phenomena at auction with the joy of winning and risk avoidance .
Only neurological imaging methods helped to resolve the contradiction between these two theories by now getting to a third explanation , ” said Andrew Schotter , professor of economics at the University of New York .
Hepatitis : When to consult a doctor ?
About half a billion people around the world suffer from chronic hepatitis B or C infection , and in Hungary , chronic liver disease is mentioned among leading causes of death .
The number of hepatitis infections in Hungary can be 100,000 , but only seven thousand are treated , because of which : patients often do not know that they are infected .
The term hepatitis is a collection name of infections caused by various viruses .
Their symptoms have many similarities , characteristic of hepatitis and jaundice , but their pathogens and diseases caused differ .
Hepatitis viruses range in two main forms depending on the pathogen : hepatitis A and E through the feed channel ( for example , infected with food , water ) , hepatitis B,C,D and other viruses with blood and body fluids ( probe , vaginal secretion , saliva ) .
Travelers should be able to protect themselves against the A and B virus with vaccine , no vaccine against C.
Symptoms of hepatitis appear two to three weeks after the consumption of the infected food , generally feeling ill , weakness , abdominal complaint , accompanied by nausea .
After this , the jaundice on the skin and the eyeswhite is formed , the stool becomes light , the urine becomes dark , the healing can take two to three weeks .
A million people die worldwide in a more severe type of disease , liver cancer and liver shrink caused by hepatitis B.
The main reason for this is that it is estimated that only every tenth infected person gets medication .
Hepatitis C may have very serious consequences : if not treated , it can lead to cirrhosis of the liver , liver cancer .
Most infected do not even know about his illness , because the pathogen destroys the liver cells intimately , in many cases , only 20 - 30 years later the first symptoms occur .
Thus , it is very important to perform early prevention , regular screening tests .
In three groups , there is much more than average disease : between people who have been through blood transfusions before 1991 , drug users and tattoos .
The number of people infected by chronic hepatitis C virus is currently 200 million in the world .
Since the disease can already be detected by a routine laboratory examination , it is worthwhile to consult a GP when detecting any symptoms of unknown origin .
Recognizing the disease in time , the virus can be exterminated from the body , thus the infestation can be eliminated and the development of cancer can be prevented .
30 September is the World Day for Hepatitis , which was held in 2004 by organisations representing patients around the world .
Its aim is to draw attention to chronic hepatitis caused by viruses , the causes of its development and the importance of early detection of the disease .
Whoever believes in God is less painful ?
According to a recent study , religious faith acts as a kind of painkiller , which could make the death of Catholic martyrs easier .
The scientists at Oxford University conducted an interesting experiment , studying the way the belief in God affects the perception of pain , and the British Telegraph reported .
In the framework of a rather bizarre study , 12 Catholic believers and the same many atheists were given electroshock , while all studied a painting of the Virgin Mary .
According to the results , Catholic believers were able to exclude most of the pain .
Thanks to the technology that scanned the human brain , it was also revealed that Catholics were able to activate the part of their brain that was responsible for the control of pain .
The study is the first in a series of research in which scientists , philosophers and theologians are involved in different parts of the university .
The study was conducted precisely by strengthening a sparkling device to the left hand of the experimental subject , which provided the electroshock .
Researchers asked participants to look closely at two paintings , the image of the Virgin Mary painted by Sassoferrato in the 17th century and Leonardo da Vinci in the 15th century painted Lady Hermelin .
The authors of the study hoped that the sight of the Virgin Mary would create a religious state among the believers , while the da Vinci image was chosen because it was not too different from the other and thought it was soothing .
The experimental subjects spent half an hour in an MRI scanner , during which time they received 20 electroshocks in four consecutive episodes , while either watching religious or general images .
Catholicians reported that during the sight of the Virgin Mary they felt " safe " , as they " cared for " and " calmed , peace filled them . "
While watching the religious image , 12 percent less pain was reported than when Leonardo 's creation was seen .
Miguel Farias , a psychologist who himself participated in the study , believes that a similar effect can be achieved with any powerful image , even atheists , only the right photo must be found .
" We should find a picture of someone who feels very positive about them , like a mother or a father . "
Bishop Tom Wright welcomed the results of the research .
" The practice of faith should be changed and in many cases changes our personality . " Wright added .
After the great results , the question is , if Leonardo or a similar - caliber painter show the believers a picture of a Madonna , what would it do to control their pain ?
Would the sight of the quality Virgin Mary mean even better results ?
