What would be the best way to develop technology that can avoid collisions if it was not imitation of barriers sensors in the world of nature ?
Like bees .
In the surprising project presented at CEATEC in Japan , the bumblebees gave the strategic idea to Nissan engineers to build the next generation of avoidance systems .
In cooperation with the University of Tokyo , Nissan built the BR23C bioutan - type automotive control system , a roboticized minia car , which was fitted with the properties of bees , with the ultimate goal of helping to create a system that eliminates all collisions .
During the flight , each bee creates its oval - shaped personal space , which is actually very similar to our safety barrier , explained Kazuhhiro Doi , technology PR and research and development brand manager at the exhibition .
It is important to play the role of the complex eye of the uterus , which can see in all directions in more than 300 degrees of view .
To copy the function of the complex eye , engineers touched the idea of the laser telescope .
This is the BR23C , which identifies obstacles within a 180-degree field of vision within 2 meters , calculates their distance and sends a signal to the onboard microprocessor , which immediately transforms into a action to avoid impact .
During the fractions of the second , the obstacle is detected , and then the car robot mimics the movements of the uterus , immediately changes direction by turning the wheels to avoid collision .
In any way other than the current system , this evasive maneuver is carried out in a completely intuitive way .
" If that were not so , the automotive robot could not react quickly enough to avoid obstacles " explains Toshiyuki Andoh , Head of Mobility Laboratory and the Car - Robot Project .
It should react in an instinctive way and immediately , as this technology corresponds to the most vulnerable and intra - internal layer of safety safety safety loop , a layer within which the collision is currently considered inevitable .
The whole process should reflect what a bee does in order to avoid other bees .
This process must take place in a blink of an eye .
However , in a way other than bees , the deviation can not be directed up , down or diagonally , only two - dimensional , and only towards the reversibility of wheels .
In this way , instead of the endless possibilities available for bees to avoid other bees , only rotary movement and acceleration were used here , as well as slowing down as the availability of the car robot .
BR23C uses lithium polymer batteries that are lighter and more energy density , which means they have longer life than lithium ion .
Andoh believes that the instinctive intelligent reaction is important , not the ability to process data , even less storage .
This device only has to process and respond to a few input signals per second .
There is no need to preserve them and respond to intuitive logic based on data from previous manoeuvres , so it is constantly using only a few dozen kilobytes of memory .
No gigabytes or memory of megabytes are needed .
This is the first step towards developing the technology for immediate evasion , which , according to Nissan ’s estimate , can enter production cars within ten years .
Additional application may be the possibility of integrating the unit with the GPS satellite navigation system to lead the car driver to the specified end goal by avoiding obstacles on the road .
